annotation.TEXT: The broom's hitbox is apparently not at long as it appears...
Oh, please tell me that's the Metal Blade!
Watch out! Falling spikes!
Ah. Found the hidden 1-up. The AWESOME SPREAD GUN is so good for finding hidden blocks!
Meh. Forget about those two coins.

Also, there was another version update a few days ago, to version 3.1.21. It must've just been for minor things, like bug-fixes and abbreviating the word "VERSION" on the title screen so that it's not obscured by the coin counter (it now says "VER 3.1.21").
Oh, just what I needed! Because I believe the Hard Knuckle is capable of destroying armored enemies like these Buzzies!
There's nothing clearly visible to the left, and I don't want to try making a blind leap of faith...

I'm not sure what else that update did, but unfortunately, it made my previous save file useless again, so I replayed the first five worlds again to get everybody back to what they had before once again.
The alt. skin votes included Modern Luigi, "Jaundice" Luigi (the Luigi with yellow skin), Francesca (Mega Man), Lance (Bill), and a random skin of whoever wins.

Oh, I was sent backwards that far? Nuts! Well, I'm gonna bend the rules a bit and turn on Infinite Time again. If it wasn't for me showing off stuff earlier in the level or backtracking, I'm sure I'd've had enough time.
Alright, so where did I pop up this time?
Also, that pipe that sent me backwards and Francesca's inability to slide normally didn't help.

Actually, I could've changed the skin to Atari Lance during play if I had thought about it while I was recording this. Alright, next time this character is used, I'll make sure it's with a Lance skin.
Well, I can slide by using the Charge Kick, but it's kind of a hassle, and it consumes weapon energy.
So, which of these duders should I use for world 7? Place your votes now! And try to vote for characters or skins that haven't been used much... Or vote for whoever you want, I guess.
I could probably defeat those Spike Tops with Hard Knuckles, but whatever.
The white palette makes sense, seeing how this is 6-3.
Hello, and welcome back to SMB Crossover, and what looks to be my last video of 2013!
Alright, that'll do for this episode.
Ooh, what's that?
I probably shouldn't waste time and weapon energy on those bricks.
And... I'm back! Now, since the RNG chose a Bill skin, I don't think I'll be using Bill/Lance/Probotector again today.
Now, Random won this time, so of course the skin will be random. However, it is possible to choose a random skin for a specific character, which I'll demonstrate later.
Also, as punishment for using the cheat, I'm going to intentionally fail to get fireworks this time.

Oh, yeah. I looked at videos of The Krion Conquest, and these pumpkin items are random enemy drops that recover the player's HP in that game, so that's where they're from. Also, I guess I'll show off Francesca's "Rush" now. It's the broom from TKC.
Hmm... It might be tricky to get past those Buzzies, unless I can bounce over the midair pipes!
If only I had a weapon that could destroy the Buzzies...
Alright, my second "R"! Bill's all set for power ups! Now, it looks like Special's 6-1 is similar to 6-1 of the original SMB.
You know what? I don't have much time left to be backtracking, so I'm just going to race forward now. Too bad I can't slide...
And the game has randomly chosen Mega Man's Atari skin. Neat.
Okay, what if I backtrack from here?
I had a nice dodge down there.
Alright, I have no idea where I resurfaced, so I'm gonna backtrack a bit here...
Oh, please tell me that I'm reasonably close to the end...
Oh, yeah. There was also a vote for Endless Eight, and a vote for SMB Crossover.
What? The very last pipe before the goal leads to another bonus room? And it's just like the previous ones.
That was weird. Did my "charging up" sound effect occur at a weird time there? Well, whatever. Let's Falcon Punch some Buzzies! (And Piranha Plants, too. Sure, why not?)
Now I imagine that this level will have multiple pipe bonus rooms, just like in 6-2 of the original SMB.

Oh, yeah. One change that was made with the Christmas update is that, at least on the normal difficulty, Lakitu doesn't respawn super-quickly after being killed. Now, it takes approximately 16 real-time seconds for him to respawn, just like in the original SMB.
And, with time running out, we've got TKC's boss music playing now. I've probably missed at least one bonus room. If I did, let me know!
Sweet! Got the 5000 and the 6 fireworks!
After giving it some thought, I've decided to go with Modern Luigi, since that's one of the newest skins.
And it looks like the level terrain has gone into Atari mode as well!
Looks like I gotta go down the pipe.
It doesn't work on barrels, so I might want to keep the Hard Knuckle handy for those.
I'd better clear some of those bricks out of the way before starting the boss fight.
I just have this feeling that I'm missing a hidden block or two somewhere...
Ha! Lakitu can't stand close-range spread gun shots to his face (or to his cloud)!
Oh, hey there, Eddie. How's it going?

Oh, also. While I'm thinking about it, here's Francesca using the Charge Kick, which does allow her to slide. I can't harm Buzzy with it, but I'm invincible during the Charge Kick, so I'm also safe (as long as I don't come to a stop overlapping the Buzzy).
So, I'll pick one of the other two characters that got 2 votes. Hmm... I guess I'll go with Francesca for 6-2. (How come there were no votes for Doropie?)
I doubt I can enter upside-down pipes, so I'm not going to even try.
And what if I was using a character that was incapable of breaking those blocks? Umm... There may or may not be a level design flaw here...
Aww, Super Arm again? This is so useless in most cases, since it can only be used on breakable bricks.
I don't need any "F"s. Thanks.

Now, who should I use next? Well, I think I'll pick a random Mega Man skin. Now, I didn't know you could do this until UltraLeet31337 mentioned it to me, but you can pick a random skin for a specific character by highlighting that character and hitting the "special" key.
Huh. It looks like they've changed the multi-coin block limit back down to 15 (I had 75 before I started hitting that multi-coin block). It was changed to 16 briefly before.

Alright, now here's an interesting fact... While Infinite Time is enabled, the game remembers how much time you should have left. However, upon disabling it, you'll be given a minimum of 100 seconds. (I learned this through off screen playing around.)
Up next is Luigi, I guess. But, which one? Modern Luigi or "Jaundice" (yellow skin) Luigi?
Yes, but there's no clear way to advance to the right from here. Would I have been totally stuck if I was small here?
Now, there's gonna be a music skip here since I had to temporarily pause the recording. Hopefully this won't cause an audio desync...
And, the RNG decided on Atari Bill (Aww... not Lance? Oh, well.), so I get to use my AWESOME SPREAD GUN some more! Yee-haw!!!
I definitely want to be careful since I've got a number of subweapons that I don't want to lose.
Whoa, the flag was farther away than I expected there, which would be why I only got 2000 and missed the 6 fireworks.
Wait a minute... I had to be big to break those blocks. Umm... Is the pipe reenterable?

However, I came back and rechecked that part later, and there was a horizontally moving platform that just never came on screen here that can be used to proceed with the level without going down the pipe, so I guess there is no actual flaw here.
I wonder why Francesca can't slide without the Charge Kick. Is it because she can't slide in TKC? Most likely.
Here's the second bonus room. It's not surprising that it's underwater, but it seems very similar to the first bonus room...
Alright, it's boss time, against this silly-looking Bowser! I don't know why, but this Bowser sprite amuses me!

This sure beats dying and losing all of my subweapons. However, I'm going to try not to use the Infinite Time cheat again. So, for instance, if world 7-4's supposed nasty maze ends up stumping me and I run out of time, nuts to that life!
To be continued... Oh, and Happy New Year!
Looks like I wasn't sent forward very far (assuming that's the same Buzzy I Charge Kicked through before), so let's keep going to the right now.
Nah, I don't need the machine gun, since I already have my AWESOME SPREAD GUN!
Ka-blammo!
Umm... No, that actually looks like the Screw Crusher from Mega Man 10. Huh, I thought the Screw Crusher was exclusive to Bass. Or was that changed with one of the recent version updates?
However, I certainly won't be amused if I get hammered or fire barred, so fighting from back here seems like a good idea. I just hope I don't run out of time!
The first of many bonus rooms in this level?
Yeah, I guess I'll Hard Knuckle one of these things.
3-1 votes: 1
Votes for Google to change the comment system back: At least 228,292.
Got him! Man, that was cutting it close!
Whoa, that was a risky jump.
